Fully submerge the #wooden skewers{10} in water and leave them there. Pre-heat your
#oven{} to 200 degrees.

Scrub the @sweet potato{2} but leave the nutritious skin on. Cut the potato
into finger sized wedges (big fingers!) and toss in @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Cook
on the top shelf of the oven on a #baking tray{} for ~{25%minutes} until cooked
and starting to crisp at the edges.

Cut the @baby gem lettuce{2} in half and then finely shred it widthways. Cut the
@vine tomatoes{2} in quarters, remove the seeds and then chop into tiny squares.
Trim any bits of fat from your @British chicken thighs{8} and discard. Chop your
chicken into bite-sized pieces.

Mix the @grain mustard{2} with the @honey{2}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and some
@pepper{}. Coat the chicken in the sauce and leave to marinade for ~{5-10%minutes}.

Remove the skewers from the water and thread the chicken pieces onto the skewers.

> Thread the skewer twice through each piece of chicken.

When the sweet potatoes are done, turn your #grill{} to high heat. Cook the skewers
under the grill for ~{15%minutes} until the chicken is cooked through and starting
to char.

Toss the lettuce and tomato chunks in @olive oil{1%tsp} and some @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Serve your skewers with a pile of the salad, the wedges and a nice
dollop of cooling @crème fraîche{4}.